description.title: Description
examples: Your new favorite après-ski (sans the ski) locales — fireplace, snug corners, and heart-warming fare included.

body.title: Body
examples: As a New York institution that opened in 1936, the Monkey Bar has had its share of the city’s glitz and lore. The red vinyl booths and monkey murals of this swanky Midtown spot have seen everyone from Frank Sinatra to Isadora Duncan, and with the group behind Au Cheval now in charge, you can expect an extravagant menu of steaks, handmade pastas, and classic cocktails executed to the nines.

body.title: Body
examples: Born in 1936, the heartbeat of Midtown dining with its timeless fare and iconic vibe.

body.title: Body
examples:
Monkey Bar accepts reservations up to 14 days in advance with each new day becoming available at 9 AM ET. Reservations are available for parties of 1-8 guests. We kindly ask that you do not make multiple reservations for more than one group. 

Seating for walk-in guests is available in the bar area. 

A $2.50 per person reservation fee will be added to all reservations made online. This is to secure your seats with us. Holiday fees may vary. We do not charge a reservation fee for walk-in guests.   

Reservations are not transferable and we are not obligated to honor transferred reservations.
